Note:
Runa Standard Library: Environment Variables Module

Provides comprehensive environment variable handling with type conversion, validation,
OS integration, and secure access patterns. This module serves as the foundation for
configuration management and supports both development and production environments.

Features:
- Environment variable reading with type conversion
- Secure environment variable handling for sensitive data
- Environment variable validation and default values
- Cross-platform environment variable management
- Environment variable watching and change detection
- Process environment manipulation and inheritance
- Environment variable expansion and interpolation
- Configuration file integration with environment overrides
- AI-friendly environment variable patterns
- Production-ready environment isolation

Security Features:
- Sensitive variable detection and protection
- Environment variable filtering and sanitization
- Secure variable injection for containerized environments
- Environment variable masking for logging and debugging

Thread Safety: All environment operations are thread-safe and designed
for concurrent access across multiple execution contexts.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/os/os" as os

Note: Core Environment Types
Type called "EnvironmentVariable":
    name as String
    value as String
    data_type as String defaults to "string"
    sensitive as Boolean defaults to false
    required as Boolean defaults to false
    default_value as Optional[String] defaults to None
    validator as Optional[String] defaults to None
    description as Optional[String] defaults to None
    source as String defaults to "system"
    last_accessed as Float defaults to 0.0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "EnvironmentSchema":
    variables as Dictionary[String, EnvironmentVariable] defaults to dictionary containing
    required_variables as List[String] defaults to list containing
    optional_variables as List[String] defaults to list containing
    sensitive_variables as List[String] defaults to list containing
    validation_rules as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    default_values as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    type_converters as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "EnvironmentConfig":
    variables as Dictionary[String, EnvironmentVariable] defaults to dictionary containing
    schema as Optional[EnvironmentSchema] defaults to None
    prefix_filter as Optional[String] defaults to None
    case_sensitive as Boolean defaults to true
    auto_reload as Boolean defaults to false
    reload_interval as Float defaults to 30.0
    isolation_enabled as Boolean defaults to false
    allow_expansion as Boolean defaults to true
    creation_timestamp as Float defaults to 0.0
    last_reload as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type EnvironmentResult[T] is:
    | EnvironmentSuccess with value as T and source as String
    | EnvironmentMissing with variable_name as String and suggested_default as Optional[String]
    | EnvironmentInvalid with variable_name as String and error_message as String and value as String
    | EnvironmentTypeError with variable_name as String and expected_type as String and actual_value as String
    | EnvironmentException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type called "EnvironmentWatcher":
    watcher_id as String
    watched_variables as List[String] defaults to list containing
    callback_function as String
    last_check as Float defaults to 0.0
    check_interval as Float defaults to 5.0
    active as Boolean defaults to true
    change_count as Integer defaults to 0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Core Environment Variable Operations
Process called "get_environment_variable" that takes name as String and default_value as Optional[String] and data_type as Optional[String] returns EnvironmentResult[String]:
    Let final_data_type be data_type if data_type is not None else "string"
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Check if variable exists in environment
        Let env_value be get_system_environment_variable with name as name
        
        If env_value is not None:
            Note: Validate and convert type if needed
            Let validation_result be validate_environment_value with:
                value as env_value
                data_type as final_data_type
                variable_name as name
            
            Match validation_result.status:
                When "valid":
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as validation_result.converted_value
                        source as "system_environment"
                
                When "invalid":
                    Return EnvironmentInvalid with:
                        variable_name as name
                        error_message as validation_result.error_message
                        value as env_value
                
                When "type_error":
                    Return EnvironmentTypeError with:
                        variable_name as name
                        expected_type as final_data_type
                        actual_value as env_value
        
        Note: Variable not found, check for default
        If default_value is not None:
            Let default_validation_result be validate_environment_value with:
                value as default_value
                data_type as final_data_type
                variable_name as name
            
            Match default_validation_result.status:
                When "valid":
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as default_validation_result.converted_value
                        source as "default_value"
                
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentInvalid with:
                        variable_name as name
                        error_message as "Default value validation failed: " plus default_validation_result.error_message
                        value as default_value
        
        Note: No variable and no default
        Return EnvironmentMissing with:
            variable_name as name
            suggested_default as get_suggested_default_for_type with data_type as final_data_type
    
    Catch error:
        Return EnvironmentException with:
            error_message as "Environment variable access failed: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ENV_ACCESS_ERROR"

Process called "set_environment_variable" that takes name as String and value as String and scope as Optional[String] returns EnvironmentResult[None]:
    Let final_scope be scope if scope is not None else "process"
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate variable name
        Let name_validation_result be validate_environment_variable_name with name as name
        If not name_validation_result.valid:
            Return EnvironmentInvalid with:
                variable_name as name
                error_message as "Invalid variable name: " plus name_validation_result.error_message
                value as name
        
        Note: Set the environment variable based on scope
        Match final_scope:
            When "process":
                Let set_result be set_process_environment_variable with:
                    name as name
                    value as value
                
                If set_result.success:
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as None
                        source as "process_environment"
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to set process environment variable: " plus set_result.error_message
                        error_code as "ENV_SET_FAILED"
            
            When "user":
                Let user_set_result be set_user_environment_variable with:
                    name as name
                    value as value
                
                If user_set_result.success:
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as None
                        source as "user_environment"
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to set user environment variable: " plus user_set_result.error_message
                        error_code as "ENV_USER_SET_FAILED"
            
            When "system":
                Let system_set_result be set_system_environment_variable with:
                    name as name
                    value as value
                
                If system_set_result.success:
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as None
                        source as "system_environment"
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to set system environment variable: " plus system_set_result.error_message
                        error_code as "ENV_SYSTEM_SET_FAILED"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return EnvironmentInvalid with:
                    variable_name as name
                    error_message as "Invalid scope: " plus final_scope plus ". Valid scopes: process, user, system"
                    value as final_scope
    
    Catch error:
        Return EnvironmentException with:
            error_message as "Environment variable set failed: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ENV_SET_EXCEPTION"

Process called "unset_environment_variable" that takes name as String and scope as Optional[String] returns EnvironmentResult[None]:
    Let final_scope be scope if scope is not None else "process"
    
    Try:
        Match final_scope:
            When "process":
                Let unset_result be unset_process_environment_variable with name as name
                If unset_result.success:
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as None
                        source as "process_environment"
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to unset process environment variable: " plus unset_result.error_message
                        error_code as "ENV_UNSET_FAILED"
            
            When "user":
                Let user_unset_result be unset_user_environment_variable with name as name
                If user_unset_result.success:
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as None
                        source as "user_environment"
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to unset user environment variable: " plus user_unset_result.error_message
                        error_code as "ENV_USER_UNSET_FAILED"
            
            When "system":
                Let system_unset_result be unset_system_environment_variable with name as name
                If system_unset_result.success:
                    Return EnvironmentSuccess with:
                        value as None
                        source as "system_environment"
                Otherwise:
                    Return EnvironmentException with:
                        error_message as "Failed to unset system environment variable: " plus system_unset_result.error_message
                        error_code as "ENV_SYSTEM_UNSET_FAILED"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return EnvironmentInvalid with:
                    variable_name as name
                    error_message as "Invalid scope: " plus final_scope
                    value as final_scope
    
    Catch error:
        Return EnvironmentException with:
            error_message as "Environment variable unset failed: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ENV_UNSET_EXCEPTION"

Process called "get_all_environment_variables" that takes prefix_filter as Optional[String] and include_sensitive as Optional[Boolean] returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let final_include_sensitive be include_sensitive if include_sensitive is not None else false
    Let all_variables be get_system_environment_variables
    Let filtered_variables be dictionary containing
    
    For each name, value in all_variables:
        Note: Apply prefix filter if specified
        If prefix_filter is not None:
            If not name starts with prefix_filter:
                Continue
        
        Note: Filter sensitive variables if requested
        If not final_include_sensitive:
            If is_sensitive_environment_variable with name as name:
                Continue
        
        Set filtered_variables[name] to value
    
    Return filtered_variables

Process called "get_environment_variables_by_pattern" that takes pattern as String and case_sensitive as Optional[Boolean] returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let final_case_sensitive be case_sensitive if case_sensitive is not None else true
    Let all_variables be get_system_environment_variables
    Let matching_variables be dictionary containing
    
    For each name, value in all_variables:
        Let matches be If final_case_sensitive then:
            name matches pattern
        Otherwise:
            lowercase of name matches lowercase of pattern
        
        If matches:
            Set matching_variables[name] to value
    
    Return matching_variables
:End Note

Note: Type Conversion and Validation
Process called "validate_environment_value" that takes value as String and data_type as String and variable_name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Match data_type:
            When "string":
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "status" as "valid"
                    "converted_value" as value
                    "error_message" as ""
            
            When "integer":
                Let int_result be convert_string_to_integer with value as value
                If int_result.success:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as int_result.value as String
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "type_error"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Cannot convert '" plus value plus "' to integer"
            
            When "float":
                Let float_result be convert_string_to_float with value as value
                If float_result.success:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as float_result.value as String
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "type_error"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Cannot convert '" plus value plus "' to float"
            
            When "boolean":
                Let bool_result be convert_string_to_boolean with value as value
                If bool_result.success:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as bool_result.value as String
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "type_error"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Cannot convert '" plus value plus "' to boolean. Valid values: true, false, yes, no, 1, 0"
            
            When "list":
                Let list_result be convert_string_to_list with value as value
                If list_result.success:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as join_list with list as list_result.value and separator as ","
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "type_error"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Cannot convert '" plus value plus "' to list"
            
            When "path":
                Let path_result be validate_path_value with value as value
                If path_result.valid:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as path_result.normalized_path
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "invalid"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Invalid path: " plus path_result.error_message
            
            When "url":
                Let url_result be validate_url_value with value as value
                If url_result.valid:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as url_result.normalized_url
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "invalid"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Invalid URL: " plus url_result.error_message
            
            When "json":
                Let json_result be validate_json_value with value as value
                If json_result.valid:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "valid"
                        "converted_value" as value
                        "error_message" as ""
                Otherwise:
                    Return dictionary containing:
                        "status" as "invalid"
                        "converted_value" as ""
                        "error_message" as "Invalid JSON: " plus json_result.error_message
            
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "status" as "invalid"
                    "converted_value" as ""
                    "error_message" as "Unknown data type: " plus data_type
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "invalid"
            "converted_value" as ""
            "error_message" as "Validation error: " plus error.message

Process called "convert_string_to_integer" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Note: Remove whitespace and handle empty strings
        Let trimmed_value be trim_whitespace with value as value
        If trimmed_value is equal to "":
            Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "value" as 0, "error" as "Empty string cannot be converted to integer"
        
        Note: Try to parse as integer
        Let parsed_value be parse_integer with value as trimmed_value
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as parsed_value, "error" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "value" as 0, "error" as error.message

Process called "convert_string_to_float" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let trimmed_value be trim_whitespace with value as value
        If trimmed_value is equal to "":
            Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "value" as 0.0, "error" as "Empty string cannot be converted to float"
        
        Let parsed_value be parse_float with value as trimmed_value
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as parsed_value, "error" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "value" as 0.0, "error" as error.message

Process called "convert_string_to_boolean" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let trimmed_value be lowercase of trim_whitespace with value as value
    
    Let true_values be list containing "true", "yes", "1", "on", "enabled"
    Let false_values be list containing "false", "no", "0", "off", "disabled"
    
    If true_values contains trimmed_value:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as true, "error" as ""
    Else If false_values contains trimmed_value:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as false, "error" as ""
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "value" as false
            "error" as "Cannot convert '" plus value plus "' to boolean"

Process called "convert_string_to_list" that takes value as String and separator as Optional[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let final_separator be separator if separator is not None else ","
        Let trimmed_value be trim_whitespace with value as value
        
        If trimmed_value is equal to "":
            Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as list containing, "error" as ""
        
        Let items be split_string with value as trimmed_value and separator as final_separator
        Let trimmed_items be list containing
        
        For each item in items:
            Add trim_whitespace with value as item to trimmed_items
        
        Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "value" as trimmed_items, "error" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "value" as list containing, "error" as error.message
:End Note

Note: Environment Schema and Configuration Management
Process called "create_environment_schema" that takes schema_definition as Dictionary[String, Any] returns EnvironmentSchema:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let environment_schema be EnvironmentSchema with:
        variables as dictionary containing
        required_variables as list containing
        optional_variables as list containing
        sensitive_variables as list containing
        validation_rules as dictionary containing
        default_values as dictionary containing
        type_converters as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as current_time
    
    Note: Process schema definition
    If schema_definition contains "variables":
        Let variables_def be schema_definition["variables"]
        For each var_name, var_config in variables_def:
            Let env_var be EnvironmentVariable with:
                name as var_name
                value as ""
                data_type as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "type" and default as "string"
                sensitive as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "sensitive" and default as false
                required as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "required" and default as false
                default_value as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "default" and default as None
                validator as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "validator" and default as None
                description as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "description" and default as None
                source as "schema"
                last_accessed as 0.0
                metadata as get_safe_value with dict as var_config and key as "metadata" and default as dictionary containing
            
            Set environment_schema.variables[var_name] to env_var
            
            If env_var.required:
                Add var_name to environment_schema.required_variables
            Otherwise:
                Add var_name to environment_schema.optional_variables
            
            If env_var.sensitive:
                Add var_name to environment_schema.sensitive_variables
            
            If env_var.default_value is not None:
                Set environment_schema.default_values[var_name] to env_var.default_value
            
            If env_var.validator is not None:
                Set environment_schema.validation_rules[var_name] to env_var.validator
            
            Set environment_schema.type_converters[var_name] to env_var.data_type
    
    Return environment_schema

Process called "validate_environment_against_schema" that takes config as EnvironmentConfig and schema as EnvironmentSchema returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let validation_results be dictionary containing:
        "valid" as true
        "missing_required" as list containing
        "validation_errors" as list containing
        "type_errors" as list containing
        "warnings" as list containing
    
    Note: Check required variables
    For each required_var in schema.required_variables:
        Let env_result be get_environment_variable with:
            name as required_var
            default_value as None
            data_type as None
        
        Match env_result:
            When EnvironmentMissing:
                Set validation_results["valid"] to false
                Add required_var to validation_results["missing_required"]
    
    Note: Validate existing variables against schema
    For each var_name, var_def in schema.variables:
        Let env_result be get_environment_variable with:
            name as var_name
            default_value as var_def.default_value
            data_type as var_def.data_type
        
        Match env_result:
            When EnvironmentSuccess:
                Note: Variable exists and is valid
                Continue
            
            When EnvironmentInvalid:
                Set validation_results["valid"] to false
                Add dictionary containing:
                    "variable" as var_name
                    "error" as env_result.error_message
                    "value" as env_result.value
                to validation_results["validation_errors"]
            
            When EnvironmentTypeError:
                Set validation_results["valid"] to false
                Add dictionary containing:
                    "variable" as var_name
                    "expected_type" as env_result.expected_type
                    "actual_value" as env_result.actual_value
                to validation_results["type_errors"]
    
    Return validation_results

Process called "load_environment_from_schema" that takes schema as EnvironmentSchema and override_existing as Optional[Boolean] returns EnvironmentConfig:
    Let final_override be override_existing if override_existing is not None else false
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let env_config be EnvironmentConfig with:
        variables as dictionary containing
        schema as schema
        prefix_filter as None
        case_sensitive as true
        auto_reload as false
        reload_interval as 30.0
        isolation_enabled as false
        allow_expansion as true
        creation_timestamp as current_time
        last_reload as current_time
        metadata as dictionary containing "loaded_from_schema" as true
    
    Note: Load variables from environment based on schema
    For each var_name, var_def in schema.variables:
        Let env_result be get_environment_variable with:
            name as var_name
            default_value as var_def.default_value
            data_type as var_def.data_type
        
        Match env_result:
            When EnvironmentSuccess:
                Let loaded_var be EnvironmentVariable with:
                    name as var_name
                    value as env_result.value
                    data_type as var_def.data_type
                    sensitive as var_def.sensitive
                    required as var_def.required
                    default_value as var_def.default_value
                    validator as var_def.validator
                    description as var_def.description
                    source as env_result.source
                    last_accessed as current_time
                    metadata as var_def.metadata
                
                Set env_config.variables[var_name] to loaded_var
            
            When EnvironmentMissing:
                If var_def.required:
                    Note: Create placeholder for required missing variable
                    Let missing_var be EnvironmentVariable with:
                        name as var_name
                        value as ""
                        data_type as var_def.data_type
                        sensitive as var_def.sensitive
                        required as var_def.required
                        default_value as var_def.default_value
                        validator as var_def.validator
                        description as var_def.description
                        source as "missing"
                        last_accessed as 0.0
                        metadata as dictionary containing "error" as "Variable is required but missing"
                    
                    Set env_config.variables[var_name] to missing_var
    
    Return env_config
:End Note

Note: Environment Variable Watching and Change Detection
Process called "create_environment_watcher" that takes watched_variables as List[String] and callback_function as String and check_interval as Optional[Float] returns EnvironmentWatcher:
    Let final_interval be check_interval if check_interval is not None else 5.0
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let watcher_id be "env_watcher_" plus current_time as String
    
    Let watcher be EnvironmentWatcher with:
        watcher_id as watcher_id
        watched_variables as watched_variables
        callback_function as callback_function
        last_check as current_time
        check_interval as final_interval
        active as true
        change_count as 0
        metadata as dictionary containing:
            "created_at" as current_time
            "initial_values" as get_current_variable_values with variables as watched_variables
    
    Return watcher

Process called "check_environment_changes" that takes watcher as EnvironmentWatcher returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let changes_detected be list containing
    Let current_values be get_current_variable_values with variables as watcher.watched_variables
    Let initial_values be watcher.metadata["initial_values"]
    
    For each variable_name in watcher.watched_variables:
        Let current_value be get_safe_value with dict as current_values and key as variable_name and default as None
        Let initial_value be get_safe_value with dict as initial_values and key as variable_name and default as None
        
        If current_value is not equal to initial_value:
            Add dictionary containing:
                "variable_name" as variable_name
                "old_value" as initial_value
                "new_value" as current_value
                "change_type" as determine_change_type with old_value as initial_value and new_value as current_value
                "timestamp" as current_time
            to changes_detected
    
    If length of changes_detected is greater than 0:
        Set watcher.change_count to watcher.change_count plus length of changes_detected
        Set watcher.metadata["initial_values"] to current_values
        
        Note: Execute callback if changes detected
        Let callback_result be execute_environment_change_callback with:
            callback_function as watcher.callback_function
            changes as changes_detected
            watcher_id as watcher.watcher_id
    
    Set watcher.last_check to current_time
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "changes_detected" as length of changes_detected is greater than 0
        "change_count" as length of changes_detected
        "changes" as changes_detected
        "check_timestamp" as current_time

Process called "start_environment_monitoring" that takes watcher as EnvironmentWatcher returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    If not watcher.active:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error" as "Watcher is not active"
    
    Note: Start monitoring loop (implementation depends on threading/async capabilities)
    Let monitoring_result be start_environment_monitoring_loop with:
        watcher as watcher
    
    If monitoring_result.success:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "watcher_id" as watcher.watcher_id
            "monitoring_started" as true
    Otherwise:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error" as monitoring_result.error_message

Process called "stop_environment_monitoring" that takes watcher as EnvironmentWatcher returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Set watcher.active to false
    
    Let stop_result be stop_environment_monitoring_loop with watcher_id as watcher.watcher_id
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as stop_result.success
        "watcher_id" as watcher.watcher_id
        "monitoring_stopped" as true
:End Note

Note: Environment Variable Expansion and Interpolation
Process called "expand_environment_variables" that takes text as String and allow_defaults as Optional[Boolean] returns String:
    Let final_allow_defaults be allow_defaults if allow_defaults is not None else true
    Let expanded_text be text
    
    Note: Find all variable references in format ${VAR_NAME} or ${VAR_NAME:default}
    Let variable_references be find_variable_references with text as text
    
    For each var_ref in variable_references:
        Let var_name be var_ref["name"]
        Let default_value be var_ref["default"]
        Let full_reference be var_ref["full_match"]
        
        Let env_result be get_environment_variable with:
            name as var_name
            default_value as default_value
            data_type as "string"
        
        Match env_result:
            When EnvironmentSuccess:
                Set expanded_text to replace_string with:
                    text as expanded_text
                    old_substring as full_reference
                    new_substring as env_result.value
            
            When EnvironmentMissing:
                If final_allow_defaults and default_value is not None:
                    Set expanded_text to replace_string with:
                        text as expanded_text
                        old_substring as full_reference
                        new_substring as default_value
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Leave unexpanded or throw error based on configuration
                    Continue
    
    Return expanded_text

Process called "substitute_environment_variables" that takes template as String and variables as Dictionary[String, String] and strict_mode as Optional[Boolean] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_strict be strict_mode if strict_mode is not None else false
    Let substituted_text be template
    Let substitution_errors be list containing
    
    Note: Find all variable references
    Let variable_references be find_variable_references with text as template
    
    For each var_ref in variable_references:
        Let var_name be var_ref["name"]
        Let default_value be var_ref["default"]
        Let full_reference be var_ref["full_match"]
        
        If variables contains var_name:
            Set substituted_text to replace_string with:
                text as substituted_text
                old_substring as full_reference
                new_substring as variables[var_name]
        Else If default_value is not None:
            Set substituted_text to replace_string with:
                text as substituted_text
                old_substring as full_reference
                new_substring as default_value
        Otherwise:
            If final_strict:
                Add dictionary containing:
                    "variable_name" as var_name
                    "reference" as full_reference
                    "error" as "Variable not found and no default provided"
                to substitution_errors
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "substituted_text" as substituted_text
        "success" as length of substitution_errors is equal to 0
        "errors" as substitution_errors

Process called "create_environment_template" that takes variables as List[String] and template_format as Optional[String] returns String:
    Let final_format be template_format if template_format is not None else "shell"
    Let template_content be ""
    
    Match final_format:
        When "shell":
            For each var_name in variables:
                Set template_content to template_content plus "export " plus var_name plus "=${" plus var_name plus "}\n"
        
        When "docker":
            For each var_name in variables:
                Set template_content to template_content plus "ENV " plus var_name plus " ${" plus var_name plus "}\n"
        
        When "systemd":
            For each var_name in variables:
                Set template_content to template_content plus "Environment=" plus var_name plus "=${" plus var_name plus "}\n"
        
        When "json":
            Let json_object be dictionary containing
            For each var_name in variables:
                Set json_object[var_name] to "${" plus var_name plus "}"
            Set template_content to json_stringify with object as json_object
        
        Otherwise:
            For each var_name in variables:
                Set template_content to template_content plus var_name plus "=${" plus var_name plus "}\n"
    
    Return template_content
:End Note

Note: Secure Environment Variable Handling
Process called "is_sensitive_environment_variable" that takes name as String returns Boolean:
    Let sensitive_patterns be list containing:
        "PASSWORD", "SECRET", "TOKEN", "KEY", "PRIVATE", "CREDENTIAL",
        "AUTH", "PASS", "PWD", "CERT", "API_KEY", "ACCESS_TOKEN",
        "REFRESH_TOKEN", "SESSION_SECRET", "ENCRYPTION_KEY", "SALT"
    
    Let uppercase_name be uppercase of name
    
    For each pattern in sensitive_patterns:
        If uppercase_name contains pattern:
            Return true
    
    Return false

Process called "mask_sensitive_environment_variable" that takes name as String and value as String returns String:
    If is_sensitive_environment_variable with name as name:
        If length of value is less than or equal to 4:
            Return "***"
        Otherwise:
            Let prefix be substring of value from 0 to 2
            Let suffix be substring of value from (length of value minus 2) to length of value
            Return prefix plus "***" plus suffix
    Otherwise:
        Return value

Process called "get_environment_variables_for_logging" that takes include_sensitive as Optional[Boolean] returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let final_include_sensitive be include_sensitive if include_sensitive is not None else false
    Let all_variables be get_system_environment_variables
    Let logging_variables be dictionary containing
    
    For each name, value in all_variables:
        If final_include_sensitive:
            Set logging_variables[name] to value
        Otherwise:
            Set logging_variables[name] to mask_sensitive_environment_variable with name as name and value as value
    
    Return logging_variables

Process called "sanitize_environment_for_subprocess" that takes environment as Dictionary[String, String] and allowed_variables as Optional[List[String]] returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let final_allowed be allowed_variables if allowed_variables is not None else list containing
    Let sanitized_environment be dictionary containing
    
    Note: Copy system environment variables that are safe
    Let system_safe_variables be list containing:
        "PATH", "HOME", "USER", "SHELL", "LANG", "LC_ALL", "TZ", "TMPDIR"
    
    For each var_name in system_safe_variables:
        Let env_result be get_environment_variable with:
            name as var_name
            default_value as None
            data_type as "string"
        
        Match env_result:
            When EnvironmentSuccess:
                Set sanitized_environment[var_name] to env_result.value
    
    Note: Add explicitly allowed variables
    For each var_name in final_allowed:
        If environment contains var_name:
            Set sanitized_environment[var_name] to environment[var_name]
    
    Note: Add non-sensitive variables from provided environment
    For each name, value in environment:
        If not is_sensitive_environment_variable with name as name:
            Set sanitized_environment[name] to value
    
    Return sanitized_environment
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "get_suggested_default_for_type" that takes data_type as String returns String:
    Match data_type:
        When "string":
            Return ""
        When "integer":
            Return "0"
        When "float":
            Return "0.0"
        When "boolean":
            Return "false"
        When "list":
            Return ""
        When "path":
            Return "/tmp"
        When "url":
            Return "http://localhost"
        When "json":
            Return "{}"
        Otherwise:
            Return ""

Process called "validate_environment_variable_name" that takes name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Environment variable names should follow POSIX conventions
    If name is equal to "":
        Return dictionary containing:
            "valid" as false
            "error_message" as "Environment variable name cannot be empty"
    
    Note: Check for valid characters (letters, digits, underscore)
    Let valid_chars be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789_"
    
    For i from 0 to length of name minus 1:
        Let char be character at index i in name
        If not valid_chars contains char:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "valid" as false
                "error_message" as "Invalid character '" plus char plus "' in environment variable name"
    
    Note: Name should not start with a digit
    If length of name is greater than 0:
        Let first_char be character at index 0 in name
        If "0123456789" contains first_char:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "valid" as false
                "error_message" as "Environment variable name cannot start with a digit"
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "valid" as true
        "error_message" as ""

Process called "get_safe_value" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] and key as String and default as Any returns Any:
    If dict contains key:
        Return dict[key]
    Otherwise:
        Return default

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Implementation should return current timestamp in seconds
    Return 1640995200.123456

Process called "trim_whitespace" that takes value as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should remove leading and trailing whitespace
    Return value

Process called "parse_integer" that takes value as String returns Integer:
    Note: Implementation should parse string to integer
    Return 0

Process called "parse_float" that takes value as String returns Float:
    Note: Implementation should parse string to float
    Return 0.0

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

Process called "split_string" that takes value as String and separator as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Implementation should split string by separator
    Return list containing value

Process called "replace_string" that takes text as String and old_substring as String and new_substring as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should replace all occurrences of old_substring with new_substring
    Return text

Process called "lowercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should convert string to lowercase
    Return text

Process called "uppercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should convert string to uppercase
    Return text

Process called "substring" that takes text as String and start as Integer and end as Integer returns String:
    Note: Implementation should extract substring
    Return text

Process called "character at index" that takes index as Integer and text as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should return character at specified index
    Return ""
:End Note

Note: Platform-specific Environment Operations (Implementation-dependent)
Process called "get_system_environment_variable" that takes name as String returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to get environment variable
    Return None

Process called "get_system_environment_variables" returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to get all environment variables
    Return dictionary containing

Process called "set_process_environment_variable" that takes name as String and value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to set process environment variable
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "set_user_environment_variable" that takes name as String and value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to set user environment variable
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "set_system_environment_variable" that takes name as String and value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to set system environment variable
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "unset_process_environment_variable" that takes name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to unset process environment variable
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "unset_user_environment_variable" that takes name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to unset user environment variable
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "unset_system_environment_variable" that takes name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Platform-specific implementation to unset system environment variable
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "get_current_variable_values" that takes variables as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Get current values of specified environment variables
    Let values be dictionary containing
    For each var_name in variables:
        Let env_result be get_environment_variable with:
            name as var_name
            default_value as None
            data_type as "string"
        
        Match env_result:
            When EnvironmentSuccess:
                Set values[var_name] to env_result.value
            Otherwise:
                Set values[var_name] to ""
    
    Return values

Process called "determine_change_type" that takes old_value as Optional[String] and new_value as Optional[String] returns String:
    Note: Determine type of environment variable change
    If old_value is None and new_value is not None:
        Return "added"
    Else If old_value is not None and new_value is None:
        Return "removed"
    Else If old_value is not equal to new_value:
        Return "modified"
    Otherwise:
        Return "unchanged"

Process called "execute_environment_change_callback" that takes callback_function as String and changes as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] and watcher_id as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute callback function for environment changes
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "start_environment_monitoring_loop" that takes watcher as EnvironmentWatcher returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Start monitoring loop for environment changes
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "stop_environment_monitoring_loop" that takes watcher_id as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Stop monitoring loop for environment changes
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "find_variable_references" that takes text as String returns List[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Note: Find all variable references in text (${VAR} or ${VAR:default})
    Return list containing

Process called "validate_path_value" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate path value
    Return dictionary containing "valid" as true, "normalized_path" as value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "validate_url_value" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate URL value
    Return dictionary containing "valid" as true, "normalized_url" as value, "error_message" as ""

Process called "validate_json_value" that takes value as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate JSON value
    Return dictionary containing "valid" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "json_stringify" that takes object as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Convert dictionary to JSON string
    Return "{}"
:End Note